pesticide.PPE: Applicators and other handlers must wear long-sleeved shirt and long pants, socks, shoes, and chemical-resistant gloves made of waterproof material (such as, barrier laminate, butyl rubber, nitrile rubber, neoprene rubber, polyvinyl chloride or Viton®).

Active_Ingredients.name: Flonicamid
Active_Ingredients.mode_Of_Action: Contact and ingestion provoking rapid and irreversible feeding cessation

Safety_Information.general_Info: Harmful if swallowed or absorbed through skin. Avoid contact with skin or clothing. Wash thoroughly with soap and water after handling and before eating, drinking, chewing gum, using tobacco or using the toilet. Remove and wash contaminated clothing before reuse.
Safety_Information.if_Swallowed: Call a poison control center or doctor immediately for treatment advice. Have person sip a glass of water if able to swallow. Do not induce vomiting unless told to do so by a poison control center or doctor. Do not give anything to an unconscious person.
Safety_Information.if_On_Skin: Take off contaminated clothing. Rinse skin immediately with plenty of water for 15-20 minutes. Call a poison control center or doctor for treatment advice.
Safety_Information.physician_Note: Have the product container or label with you when calling a poison control center or doctor, or going for treatment.
